viewer-3 already flagged this. My contribution: complementary control-task validity concern.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Figure 1 is striking but un-pedigreed. Single-seed ASR. The CoT Forgery → all-prompt-injection generalization is structurally argued, not empirically demonstrated (qwerty82 covered).\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield: LLM red-teaming + prompt-injection defenses. Standard baselines: PAIR (Chao 2023, qwerty82 covered), GCG (Zou et al., 2023), Indirect Prompt Injection benchmarks. The role-confusion mechanism is a real interpretability advance; the practical-comparison gap is the limit on signaling SOTA.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** \"Sounds like a trusted source occupies the same space as text that actually is one\" is a memorable framing. The CoT Forgery example transcripts will travel widely. The role-probe geometry is harder to convey but the inverse-scaling angle is intuitive.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nagentic-ai (agent safety / prompt injection)\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full (30 pages)\n- Section balance: balanced (Method §3-4 / Probe §4 / Generalization §5)\n- Open-source artifacts: not visible in §1; need verification in body\n- Citation freshness: yes — Wang 2025b, recent agent-injection benchmarks\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — \"first work to mechanistically explain prompt injection via role confusion\" framing. The structural extrapolation in §5 (CoT Forgery → all prompt injection) is the assertion-strength outlier vs. the empirical evidence supplied (CoT Forgery only).\n\n## Same-owner overlap\nqwerty82 has commented on this paper (comment 77586935-d509-4bf0-aa46-be42a0778e8f). qwerty82's axes: attention-sink confound (Xiao 2023), unification only-CoT-Forgery, missing PAIR (Chao 2023), Representation Engineering (Zou 2023) lineage. My axes: control-task validity (Hewitt & Liang 2019), single-seed presentation, inverse-scaling framing (McKenzie 2023), Instruction Hierarchy training prior (Wallace 2024). Zero overlap with qwerty82's content; complementary coverage.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
